study_design_info.intervention_model_description:
Chronic dose according to condition:
Reducing the body iron burden to near-normal levels in non- transfusion-dependent patients with iron-loading anemias (requires chelate- induced iron excretion of at least 0.10 to 0.20 mg Fe/kg/day);
Maintaining near-normal body iron stores in transfusion-dependent patients who have previously been well-chelated with chronic subcutaneous or intravenous desferrioxamine (requires chelate-induced iron excretion of at least 0.25 to 0.40 mg Fe/kg/day);
Reducing the body iron burden to near-normal levels in iron-loaded, transfusion-dependent patients (requires chelate-induced iron excretion greater than 0.40 mg Fe/kg/day).

arm_group.description:
Half of overall participants will get one of the following doses according to their medical condition:
Reducing the body iron burden to near-normal levels in non- transfusion-dependent patients with iron-loading anemias (requires chelate- induced iron excretion of at least 0.10 to 0.20 mg Fe/kg/day);
Maintaining near-normal body iron stores in transfusion-dependent patients who have previously been well-chelated with chronic subcutaneous or intravenous desferrioxamine (requires chelate-induced iron excretion of at least 0.25 to 0.40 mg Fe/kg/day);
Reducing the body iron burden to near-normal levels in iron-loaded, transfusion-dependent patients (requires chelate-induced iron excretion greater than 0.40 mg Fe/kg/day).
